-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_billing_events.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate billing_events to one row per subscription and month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_id,
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- models/intermediate/int_user_with_company.sql
```sql
-- Join users with companies to get industry information
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        u.user_id,
        u.company_id,
        c.industry
    FROM {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON c.company_id = u.company_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

-- models/intermediate/int_subscription_with_plan.sql
```sql
-- Join subscriptions with plans to get tier information
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,
        p.tier,
        p.monthly_price
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = s.plan_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

-- models/intermediate/int_final_joins.sql

-- Join subscriptions with plans, users, and companies
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        sp.subscription_id,
        sp.user_id,
        sp.started_at,
        sp.ended_at,
        sp.status,
        sp.tier,
        sp.monthly_price,
        uc.industry,
        be.event_month,
        be.amount AS mrr_amount
    FROM {{ ref('int_subscription_with_plan') }} sp
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_user_with_company') }} uc
        ON uc.user_id = sp.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} be
        ON be.subscription_id = sp.subscription_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

-- models/mart/fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
```sql
-- Calculate monthly subscription metrics by tier and industry
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        COALESCE(event_month, DATE_TRUNC('month', started_at)) AS month,
        COALESCE(tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(industry, '(unknown)') AS industry,
        subscription_id,
        user_id,
        COALESCE(mrr_amount, monthly_price) AS mrr_amount,
        status
    FROM {{ ref('int_final_joins') }}
)
SELECT
    month,
    tier,
    industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(mrr_amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM source
WHERE status = 'active'
GROUP BY
    month,
    tier,
    industry
ORDER BY
    month DESC,
    tier,
    industry
